# <NAME> — Firebase backend

This project was scaffolded with Firebase wiring for auth, cloud storage, and
multiplayer state. `firebase` is installed; `src/firebase.ts` exports `app`,
`auth`, and `db` (Firestore).

## Setup

1. Create a Firebase project at <https://console.firebase.google.com>.
2. Add a **Web app**; copy its config into `.env.local` (template in `.env.example`).
3. `npm install -g firebase-tools` and `firebase login` (run from a terminal — interactive).
4. Edit `.firebaserc` — set `default` to your real Firebase project ID.

## Use

```ts
import { db, auth } from './firebase';
import { doc, setDoc, onSnapshot } from 'firebase/firestore';

// Realtime sync: subscribe to a game-room doc.
onSnapshot(doc(db, 'rooms', roomId), (snap) => render(snap.data()));
await setDoc(doc(db, 'rooms', roomId), { state }, { merge: true });
```

Firestore is great for turn-based / persistence / leaderboards. For fast
real-time action, throttle writes or layer a dedicated realtime channel.

## Deploy to Firebase Hosting

```bash
npm run build:firebase   # vite build --base=/
firebase deploy
```

Security note: `VITE_FIREBASE_*` keys are public by design — gate access with
Firestore/Storage **security rules**, not key secrecy.
